The paper deals with a probabilistic algorithmic technique, the Lovász Local Lemma, which is commonly used in computer science for solving problems related to probability and combinatorics. The paper also discusses an interactive version of the algorithm, which involves multiple parties and private coin flips. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), and probability (cs.PR).
